record_data.record_plain_text: Enel Stillwater, LLC Electric MBR Agreements Effective Date: Shared Facilities Agreement Option Code A EXHIBIT A SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT among ENEL STILLWATER, LLC EGP STILLWATER SOLAR, LLC EGP STILLWATER SOLAR PV II, LLC and ENEL GREEN POWER NORTH AMERICA, INC. November 14, 2017 SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT among ENEL STILLWATER, LLC EGP STILLWATER SOLAR, LLC EGP STILLWATER SOLAR PV II, LLC and ENEL GREEN POWER NORTH AMERICA, INC. November 14, 2017 INDEX OF EXHIBITS AND SCHEDULES Exhibit A Shared Facilities Exhibit A-1 Project Parcels Exhibit B Percentage Interest of Geo Owner, Solar I and Solar II Exhibit C Insurance Requirements Exhibit D Dispute Resolution Procedures Exhibit E Form of Memorandum of Shared Facilities Agreement Exhibit F Form of Sublease and Subeasement Agreement Exhibit G Form of Consent and Encroachment Agreement SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is entered into as of November 14, 2017 (the “Effective Date”), by and between ENEL STILLWATER, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Geo Owner”), EGP STILLWATER SOLAR, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Solar I”), and EGP STILLWATER SOLAR PV II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Solar II”) and Enel Green Power North America, Inc., a Delaware corporation (“Enel”). Each of Geo Owner, Solar I and Solar II are referred to herein as an “Owner,” and collectively Geo Owner, Solar I and Solar II are referred to as the “Owners,” in each case both in their respective capacities as owners and operators of the respective Projects, as such term is defined below. The Owners and Enel are referred to herein individually as a “Party,” as the context requires, or collectively as the “Parties”. Enel also is referred to herein as “Manager” in its capacity as the initial “Manager,” as defined below, subject to any subsequent change in the Manager in accordance with this Agreement. RECITALS: Geo Owner owns and operates a 33.1 MW rated capacity geothermal generating facility and a 2 MW concentrated solar photovoltaic generation facility located in Churchill County, Nevada and that consists of turbines, generators, wells, pipeline and associated collection and 60 kV interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the “Geo Project”). Solar I owns and operates a 26.4 MW rated capacity solar photovoltaic generation facility located in Churchill County, Nevada and that consists of solar panels, inverters, trackers and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the “Solar I Project”). Solar II desires to install, own and operate a 20 MW rated capacity solar photovoltaic generation facility located in Churchill County, Nevada and that consists of solar panels, inverters, trackers and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the “Solar II Project”), in proximity to the Solar I Project. Solar II is constructing, and will be the owner of, certain transmission facilities that will bisect the 60 kV interconnection facilities owned by Geo Owner. These additional facilities include new 60 kV taps, poles, a circuit breaker, and metering, as described and shown in more detail in Exhibit A hereto (the “New Shared Facilities”), and will be installed on or connecting into the existing transmission line on the Project Site, substation and switchyard, all owned by Geo Owner (the “Existing Shared Facilities”). Pursuant to this Agreement, each Owner will utilize the Existing Shared Facilities and the New Shared Facilities (together, the “Shared Facilities”) to interconnect its respective Project with the transmission grid owned and operated by Sierra Pacific Power Company d/b/a NV Energy (“NV-E”). Geo Owner owns, leases or holds easement rights to approximately 360 acres of land which includes the parcels more particularly described in Exhibit A-1 (“Geo Parcels”). Solar I leases approximately 120 acres of land which includes the parcels more particularly described in Exhibit A-1 (“Solar I Parcels”). Solar II will lease certain parcels from Geo Owner and certain parcels from an unrelated party, totaling approximately 200 acres of land which includes the parcels more particularly described in Exhibit A-1 (“Solar II Parcels”). Geo Parcels, Solar I Parcels, and Solar II Parcels are collectively and individually referred to herein as the “Lease Interest” and a “Lease Interest” respectively. In connection with the Shared Facilities, the parties desire to grant each other certain subeasement and/or access rights for the purposes of constructing, owning, operating and maintaining the Projects and the Shared Facilities. The Geo Parcels consist of certain real property on which the Existing Shared Facilities are located, and upon which the New Shared Facilities will be constructed as more particularly described on Exhibit A-1 (the “Shared Facilities Real Property”), and pursuant to and upon the collective execution of this Agreement and the execution and recording of a separate Sublease and Subeasement Agreement by and between Geo Owner and Solar II, granting access to the Shared Facilities as set forth and described below, Geo Owner shall grant Solar II certain rights necessary to construct and use the New Shared Facilities and access and use the Existing Shared Facilities on the Shared Facilities Real Property in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Geo Owner, Solar I and Solar II desire for Geo Owner, with respect to the Existing Shared Facilities, and Solar II, with respect to the New Shared Facilities, to grant the Shared Facilities jointly to the Owners to the extent needed for, and in order to support, Solar II’s development and operation of the Solar II Project and the ongoing operation of all of the Projects. Geo Owner and Solar II shall, concurrently with this Agreement, enter and record a separate Consent and Encroachment Agreement, wherein Geo Owner and Solar II shall each grant the other Party consent to use Shared Facilities Real Property and any other real property where both Geo Owner and Solar II have, or shall have, an interest for the other Party’s respective use, activities and operations to and on such real property, in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Solar I and Solar II shall, concurrently with this Agreement, enter and record a separate Consent and Encroachment Agreement, wherein Solar I and Solar II shall each grant the other Party consent to use Shared Facilities Real Property and any other real property where both Solar I and Solar II have, or shall have, an interest for the other Party’s respective use, activities and operations to and on such real property, in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. The Parties wish to set forth herein their respective rights and obligations regarding such joint use, maintenance, repair, replacement of, and alterations to the Shared Facilities. The Parties also wish to provide for the appointment of a Manager for the provision of certain services with respect to the Shared Facilities, at such time and on the terms and conditions contained herein. Rules of Interpretation. Titles, captions and headings in this Agreement are inserted for convenience only and will not be used for the purposes of construing or interpreting this Agreement. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (i) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (ii) reference to any Person includes such Person’s successors and assigns but, in the case of a Party, only if such successors and assigns are permitted by this Agreement (except to the extent explicitly provided otherwise), and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (iii) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (iv) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (v) reference to any law means such law as amended, modified, codified or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (vi) reference to any Article or Section means such Article or Section of this Agreement, and references in any Article, Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Article, Section or definition; (vii) “hereunder,” “hereof,” “hereto” and words of similar import will be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Article, Section or other provision of this Agreement; (viii) “including” (and with correlative meaning “include”) means including without limiting the generality of any description preceding such term; and (ix) relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “from and including”, “to” means “to but excluding” and “through” means “through and including”. Words and abbreviations not defined in this Agreement that have well-known technical or power industry meanings in the United States are used in this Agreement in accordance with those recognized meanings. This Agreement was negotiated and prepared by the Parties with advice of counsel to the extent deemed necessary by each Party. The Parties have agreed to the wording of this Agreement, and none of the provisions of this Agreement will be construed against one Party on the ground that such Party is the author of this Agreement or any part of this Agreement. TERM; PURCHASE PRICE; AND CONDITIONS PRECEDENT Effective Date. This Agreement will commence on the Effective Date and remain in full force and effect following the Effective Date until the first occurrence of (a) the mutual agreement of all of the Parties to terminate this Agreement, or (b) otherwise as provided under this Agreement. Conditions Precedent to Shared Use. This Agreement shall be filed with FERC for acceptance under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act with a requested effective date prior to Solar II’s use of the Shared Facilities. GRANT OF SUBLEASE AND SUBEASEMENT RIGHTS Shared Easement Rights. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the separate Sublease and Sublease Agreement as further described below, Geo Owner hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants jointly to Solar I and Solar II and their respective successors and assigns, for the benefit of and appurtenant to the Shared Facilities, the Shared Facilities Real Property, the Geo Parcels, the Solar I Parcels, the Solar II Parcels, the Solar I Project and the Solar II Project, sub-easement and sublease rights over, across and under the Shared Facilities Real Property for the purpose of accessing, constructing, operating, repairing, improving, upgrading and maintaining the Shared Facilities and related structures and ingress and egress access thereto as necessary and to the extent such rights are granted to Geo Owner pursuant to the Geo Parcels (the “Shared Easement Rights”). Geo Owner, Solar I and Solar II shall record in the land registry records of the County of Churchill, State of Nevada, the Memorandum of Shared Facilities Agreement as further described herein and set forth in Exhibit E hereto. Separate Agreement. Geo Owner and Solar II shall execute and record in the land registry records of the County of Churchill, State of Nevada, a separate Sublease and Subeasement Agreement in substantially similar form to the Sublease and Sublease Agreement annexed hereto and made a part hereof as Exhibit F by and between Geo Owner and Solar II, wherein Geo Owner shall grant Solar II certain rights necessary to construct and use the New Shared Facilities and access and use the Existing Shared Facilities on the Shared Facilities Real Property. Notice and Cure Rights. The Manager or the Owners shall promptly notify the Manager or the other Owners, respectively, of any notices of default from any landowners to the Manager with respect to any underlying leases or easements constituting the Shared Easement Rights, and each Owner shall have the right, but not the obligation, to cure any such defaults. SHARED FACILITIES Shared Facilities. The Owners shall each own an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities, as tenants in common in proportion to their Percentage Interest, for the benefit, operation and use of its respective Project provided herein (the “Ownership Interest”). The Owners shall operate and maintain the Shared Facilities that, as of the Effective Date, are governed by this Agreement and after fulfillment of the conditions precedent set forth in Section 2.2, the Manager shall operate and maintain the Shared Facilities as further detailed herein. Grant of Rights in Shared Facilities. Grant of Interest. Upon and subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth in this Agreement, Geo Owner hereby grants to each of Solar I and Solar II its undivided Ownership Interest in and to the Existing Shared Facilities, and Solar II hereby grants to each of Geo Owner and Solar I their respective undivided Ownership Interest in and to the New Shared Facilities, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW. The result of such transfers is that each Owner owns its Ownership Interest in and to the entirety of the Shared Facilities, including the New Shared Facilities. Intentionally omitted. Bill of Sale. Simultaneous with execution of this Agreement, each of Geo Owner and Solar II shall execute a commercially reasonable form of Bill of Sale, transferring to the Owners their respective undivided Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities as provided in Section 4.2.1. Other Instruments. On the Effective Date, or within a reasonable time thereafter, the Manager and/or any Parties hereto shall deliver to the Owners, for the benefit of all of the Owners any other notices, instruments, documents, agreements or consents as are reasonably necessary in connection with the Ownership Interest or the joint ownership of the Shared Facilities. Access to Shared Facilities. Each of the Grantors and Grantees and their respective Representatives shall have access to the Shared Facilities (a) for inspection of the Shared Facilities, (b) for any required maintenance and repairs of the Shared Facilities as agreed to by the Grantors, Grantees and the Manager, if applicable, and (c) in connection with the operation of the Shared Facilities, all in accordance with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, except in the event of an Emergency, each of Grantor and Grantee shall provide no less than 24 hours’ prior notice to the other Party (and the Manager, if applicable) of its or any of its Representative’s intent to access the Shared Facilities and the planned scope of work requiring such access, and each of Grantor and Grantee shall provide no less than 48 hours’ prior notice to the other Party (and the Manager, if applicable) prior to performing any maintenance or repairs pursuant to clause (b) above. Each of Grantor and Grantee and any of their respective Representatives shall: (i) follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the Manager; and (ii) comply with all applicable real estate restrictions, applicable Law and Governmental Approvals when on the premises or accessing the Shared Facilities, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Shared Facilities to respond to the Emergency, but Grantor or Grantee (as applicable) shall provide notice of access to, and coordinate with, Manager (if applicable) and the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter. No Interference, Cooperation; Quiet Enjoyment and Over-Burdening. Each Owner’s use of the Shared Facilities or the operation of its Project shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Party of its respective rights in such Shared Facilities or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, including Section 6.14 below, each of the Owners hereby consents to the development and operation of the Projects, and each of the Owners shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the other Owner’s use of the Shared Facilities for the benefit of the Owners as contemplated by this Agreement. Interconnection. Geo Owner and Solar I acknowledge that Solar II intends to use such rights under the GIA as are necessary to interconnect the Solar II Project to the NVE-controlled transmission system and to deliver electrical energy generated by the Solar II Project. To the extent that the operation of the Projects exceeds the 56 MW maximum capacity of the Shared Facilities (the “Maximum Capacity”), Solar II shall alone curtail output from the Solar II Project in order to restore the Shared Facilities to operation at or below the Maximum Capacity. All Owners may take such actions as may be necessary to comply with any order received from a balancing authority or Governmental Authority, and nothing herein shall require the Owners to violate the requirements of any such order. Any curtailment of interconnection services directed by NVE or a Governmental Authority for reasons other than exceeding Maximum Capacity but caused by the actions or inactions of one Owner shall be allocated to the fullest extent possible to the Owner that caused such curtailment. In the event of any curtailment of interconnection services directed by NVE or a Governmental Authority for reasons other than exceeding Maximum Capacity or actions or inactions of one Owner, the Owners shall curtail in the following manner, to the extent necessary, until such curtailment is achieved: first, each Owner (if any) that is delivering energy in excess of its Project’s nameplate capacity shall reduce deliveries down to such nameplate capacity; second, each Owner will curtail pro rata in proportion to its Percentage Interest; provided that if any Project is offline during the curtailment event for routine maintenance or other reasons, the curtailment shall be allocated pro rata between the operational Projects. Notwithstanding the above, the Manager shall be authorized to curtail the Project on a non-pro rata, but equitable and reasonable basis (as determined by the Manager in good faith) if necessary to comply with the GIA or requirements of a Governmental Authority.
